Vice President Mike Pence visited the Stout Field Indiana National Guard Training Center in Indianapolis to mark Armed Forces Day and thank the service members for their dedication. Pence also addressed the recent school shooting in Santa Fe, Texas, expressing condolences and promising to take steps to ensure the safety of schools. He praised the first responders who acted heroically during the attack and expressed gratitude to all those who serve in the military. Pence's own family has a history of military service, with his wife's father serving in the Air Force, his father serving in the Army, and their son being a Marine. He concluded by wishing everyone a Happy Armed Forces Day and thanking them for their service.